Language.Sentence: The Tree type produces an object that reflexes the data structure of web pages of VDOM application as a tree of linked nodes.
The necessary CSS code applied to all objects within the container.
The order of rendering the object on the page. The objects with identical values of the Hierarchy attribute are rendered in the order they are written in the XML-file of the VDOM application.
Spacing in pixels between the object and the top border of the container, in which the object is situated.
Spacing in pixels between the object and the left border of the container, in which the object is situated.
The width of the object in pixels.
The height of the object in pixels.
The title appearance attribute. The title to display is set in the 'Title' attribute.
The title of the object to display, may be in the HTML format. In some objects the title is not displayed if the 'Title appearance' attribute is set to 'Title off'.
The data to display in the HTML format. The <li> elements must contain the 'id' attribute.

The Ajax options used to initialize the tree structure, which define the way of uploading the data. If it is defined, the object will be created with the data specified here, and the 'Data' attribute will be ignored.
Using checkboxes in order to select several items. If it is set to 'Yes' - the checkboxes will be displayed at each item, if 'No' - there will be no checkboxes.
Using the automatic collapsing of all siblings, when a node is expanded.

The way of marking the checkboxes. It works only when the 'Checkbox' attribute is turned on. If it is set to 'Single', only one item will be selected, 'Multi'---several items regardless of the items nesting; 'Multi-hier'---several items depending on the items nesting.

The position in visual hierarchy of objects. If you have several objects in one container situated on each other, the value of 'Z-Index' attribute indicates the order of their displaying. The larger the value is, the upper the object is situated.
The visibility of the object. In any case the object will exist on the web page, this attribute only makes it invisible.
